Liar
Pulling an underhanded trick!

41
00:03:21,501 --> 00:03:22,126
Liar

42
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,677
Azusa...

43
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,013
Just what kind of man is he?!

44
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:37,617
Simply described,
the infamous Mokkori man.

45
00:03:37,617 --> 00:03:41,314
Mok... He is completely insane.

46
00:03:42,021 --> 00:03:43,690
That was a mistake back there.

47
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:46,557
That was like dangling a carrot
in front of a horse's nose.

48
00:03:46,826 --> 00:03:49,420
It's typical of them, sending
me a guy like that.

49
00:03:49,662 --> 00:03:51,664
There's something wrong with those
people at the publishers!

50
00:03:51,664 --> 00:03:53,461
It would be much better to have no one at all.

51
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:56,035
Whispering like that isn't nice.

52
00:03:56,803 --> 00:04:00,173
There should be no secrets
between us, my honey.

53
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:02,004
Ryo! Back off!

54
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:08,948
Where are you going?

55
00:04:08,948 --> 00:04:10,049
Research.

56
00:04:10,049 --> 00:04:11,284
For a story?

57
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:14,185
Right, this time I'm going to do a
hard-boiled detective story.

58
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:18,113
To do it, I need to learn a lot
about the underworld.

59
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:20,219
Kanto
Kimen
Gumi

60
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,991
Just a little higher. Okay!

61
00:04:32,805 --> 00:04:36,142
If she were wearing a skirt, this
would be more enjoyable.

62
00:04:36,142 --> 00:04:37,677
Did you say something?

63
00:04:37,677 --> 00:04:38,575
No!

64
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,439
I'm in luck! No one's around. Okay...

65
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:46,448
Hey!

66
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:54,083
What the hell are you doing there?!
Tell me which gang you're from!

67
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:56,896
I'm Ryo from the Mokkori Gumi.

68
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:58,364
Son of a...

69
00:04:58,364 --> 00:04:58,931
Hold!
Son of a...

70
00:04:58,931 --> 00:04:59,829
Hold!

71
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,068
Don't be bothering those decent people.

72
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:05,330
Uh-oh...

73
00:05:14,013 --> 00:05:17,176
Don't just stand there! Show our guests in!

74
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,973
Yes, Sir!

75
00:05:23,856 --> 00:05:25,653
So many antiques.

76
00:05:26,526 --> 00:05:28,016
Please, please, come in.

77
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:35,726
A yakuza these days just can't make the
grade if he can't even draw a picture.

78
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:40,230
A broad education counts for a lot in
helping us overcome our competition.

79
00:05:41,374 --> 00:05:43,365
You're very good!

80
00:05:44,577 --> 00:05:48,414
I see you've finally decided
to take my offer, Ryo?

81
00:05:48,414 --> 00:05:50,483
My visit here today has nothing
to do with that.

82
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:54,476
Don't say such things.
Come join my organization!

83
00:05:55,588 --> 00:05:57,990
I'll pay you this much in contract fees.

84
00:05:57,990 --> 00:05:59,514
What are you whispering about?!

85
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:04,258
This young lady says she
wants to talk to you.

86
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,226
Are you a reporter or something?

87
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:08,701
I'm a novelist.

88
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:13,773
Good. Those lap dogs of the capitalists
loathe the very sight of

89
00:06:13,773 --> 00:06:15,942
we common men of the working class.

90
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:17,043
I have two or three questions...

91
